ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: How often do you have each of these experiences: You feel like a part of your university?
Notes: 0 = Never; 1 = Rarely; 2 = Sometimes; 3 = Often; 4 = Very often

ElementDescription: How often do you have each of these experiences: People in your university notice when you are good at something?
Notes: 0 = Never; 1 = Rarely; 2 = Sometimes; 3 = Often; 4 = Very often

ElementDescription: How often do you have each of these experiences: Other students take your opinions seriously?
Notes: 0 = Never; 1 = Rarely; 2 = Sometimes; 3 = Often; 4 = Very often

ElementDescription: How often do you have each of these experiences: You are included in lots of activities at your university?
Notes: 0 = Never; 1 = Rarely; 2 = Sometimes; 3 = Often; 4 = Very often

ElementDescription: How often do you have each of these experiences: Other students like you the way you are?
Notes: 0 = Never; 1 = Rarely; 2 = Sometimes; 3 = Often; 4 = Very often

ElementDescription: How often have you had problems paying for basic necessities like food, clothing, housing/rent, or transportation since you have been at university?
Notes: 0 = None of the time; 1 = A little of the time; 2 = Some of the time; 3 = Most of the time; 4 = All or almost all of the time

ElementDescription: My academic performance is...
Notes: 1 = Lower than most of my peers at university; 2 = Similar to most of my peers; 3 = Superior to most of my peers at university

ElementDescription: How likely is it that you will drop out of school before graduation?
Notes: 0 = Not at all likely; 1 = Not very; 2 = Somewhat; 3 = Very likely

ElementDescription: Timepoint/visit label
